      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:26:12",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/26/462",
      "text": [
        " اَلْحَمْلِ مِنْ جَوَانِبِهِ اَلْأَرْبَعَةِ أَوْ مَا خَفَّ عَلَى اَلرَّجُلِ يَحْمِلُ مِنْ أَيِّ اَلْجَوَانِبِ شَاءَ فَكَتَبَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ «مِنْ أَيِّهَا شَاءَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.462 - Hussein ibn Saeed wrote to Abu Al-Hasan Imam Ali ibn Musa Ar-Ridha (as), asking about the bier of the deceased: Is there a specific side that should be carried first from among its four sides, or can one carry it from any side that is easiest?\nImam (as) replied: \"From whichever side he wishes.\""
        ]
      }
    },
